<h3 id="progress-to-the-present">Progress to the present</h3>

<p>Thus far the main portion of the story has been shot, with plans to debut as a two part pilot episode. This allows us to screen publicly the first half, to thank all who participated in the early portion of shooting, we also need everyone‚Äôs help. And to make the story a cliff hanger, now we need your help to make this story complete‚Ä¶</p>

<h2 id="help-us-by-recording-webcam-videos">Help us by recording webcam videos</h2>

<p>Yes, now you can become part of our production by using any old webcam or cellphone to make a selfie video.</p>

<p>We have relative story material, but in order to make the content more substantial, we urge everyone to join our production by recording videos of YOU for us. NO acting required. In fact we want you to just be YOU.</p>

<h3 id="style-and-tone">Style and tone</h3>

<p>Many of you have seen captain‚Äôs logs, and the first officer‚Äôs log etc., but Star Trek rarely portrays a normal crew members‚Äô daily work, we intend to insert this into the main storyline.</p>

<p>Usually the communication between crew are mostly audio-based (off screen), but we wondered why not video calls? Its the future‚Ä¶imagine the feeling of being lost in space far far away from home, walking in a starship corridor with a selfie stick ‚Ä¶what would you say and think. Would you laugh, would you cry, be silly, sing, rap, attempt to solve technical ship related issues, or just complain? Who would you call?</p>

<p><strong>Record video in the form of a crew log or video call.</strong> Just face the phone / computer camera, speak and record.</p>

<p>The background can be:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Pure white / green (green curtain) wall, so that we can be process it later as if you are in the corridor, crew quarters and so on.</li>
  <li>Of course, if you can not find a white or green wall, then any solid background will also work. Light or dark background if you need to shoot from your school dorm room. We welcome you to play with your own imagination, think of all the places you could be on a starship, Make sure you don‚Äôt have things seen in frame that reflect today‚Äôs era (unless you establish yourself as a 21st century vintage retro lover). Anything you can do to make it easier for us to use and process easier will probably ensure you get more screen time.</li>
</ul>

<h3 id="sets">Sets</h3>

<p>In correlation with our episode‚Äôs storyline, you have these <strong>roles to choose</strong>:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Museum staff</li>
  <li>Ordinary tourists, with no knowledge of actual Star fleet protocol.</li>
  <li>Star Fleet Academy students</li>
  <li>Star Fleet staff</li>
</ul>

<p>Use your imagination‚Ä¶in the Star Trek Universe anything is possible and any kind of cosplay character is ok. Or just be YOU.</p>

<h4 id="general-crew-description">General crew description</h4>

<p>There are many of you who hope to work on a star ship but your Star Fleet grade is so low that you can only compromise by taking a job cleaning Enterprise‚Äôs decks or by working as a tour guide etc‚Ä¶.but you‚Äôre still excited to be there. Many of you know Star Ship and Star fleet history and technology intrinsically, but only from a text book perspective.</p>

<h4 id="the-look-and-feel">The look and feel</h4>

<p>Clothes / uniforms or makeup should ideally match your selected role, race, type of work and so on‚Ä¶but you can be more creative if it makes sense and is well‚Ä¶funny.</p>

<h3 id="order-of-events-within-the-storyline">Order of events within the storyline</h3>

<p>Chronologically, the log recordings / video calls occur as follows:</p>

<ol>
  <li><strong>Start of the work day.</strong> You are just starting work. Maybe you missed breakfast and are thinking about trivial issues, promotions, and classmate rumors.</li>
  <li><strong>The commanding officer and curator, Horatio arrives.</strong> Things become serious. No more goofing around.</li>
  <li><strong>The ship leaves dry dock, and is out of control.</strong> You feel fear / madness / any emotion‚Ä¶or maybe no emotion if you‚Äôre part Vulcan LOL.</li>
  <li><strong>The ship is controlled by unknown forces and is moving somewhere.</strong> You feel uncertainty, fear, doubt that the captain (Horatio) does not know what to do.</li>
  <li><strong>Being boarded (who boarded the ship?).</strong> You can refer to something like Q who likes to play with and control other people‚Äôs minds. Here our visitors‚Äôs names are The Cowboy, and Pepe, Whether or not to use these specific names is your choice. Maybe you don‚Äôt know their names yet.)</li>
  <li><strong>Beam down to planet.</strong> After a red shirt investigation, a box is discovered (at this time you do not know what it is). You will probably only know that it‚Äôs a box left behind by a crazy scientist who uses this box to control minds, is smaller than Landru and more hyper A.I. We won‚Äôt show you the box yet but you can guess what it looks like. Only a few of the commanders know. You‚Äôre hearing mostly here say and rumors.</li>
</ol>

<h3 id="examples-to-use">Examples to use</h3>

<p>Below are further expanded examples of some of the settings and tonalities mentioned above that may help you form the basis of your character, and mood.</p>

<p>Use colloquial language. Or even sign language. Or just cry and laugh. Language can be optional, If you speak it can be in Mandarin or English or any other known or unknown language or dialect. Choose your setting, and character, press record, and go. You can record something for all 6 order of events in the story if you like.</p>

<p>Below are a few examples to get you warmed up. Make up your own dialog though. These are examples only.</p>

<h4 id="set-no1-example-only">Set No.1 EXAMPLE ONLY</h4>

<p>Video call: ‚ÄúJack, I finally arrive in the place I‚Äôve been dreaming about for eons‚Ä¶and now after I‚Äôve completed course work in quantum mechanics, and after you completed the treatment of god knows how many diseases, we get to apply together for Star Weep Academy! I‚Äôm soooo stoked. Dude‚Ä¶we‚Äôve made it!‚Äù</p>

<p>You can <strong>add any details you want</strong>. Call any body. Call your friend who can also record a chat so both of you can contribute. If you record a number of sets in a row, you can also let the details develop. Open your imagination, Improvise, be funny, silly, or serious.</p>

<p>Messages can contain poems, thoughts, complaints, anger, fear, humor, singing, etc‚Ä¶</p>

<h4 id="set-no2-example-only">Set No.2 EXAMPLE ONLY</h4>

<p>Janitors and housekeeping: <em>‚ÄúThe big wig is in the house!!! a little coffee stain on the bridge floor will have him nagging us from here to Beta Alha 9‚Ä¶.Oh my!‚Äù</em></p>

<h4 id="set-no3-example-only">Set No.3 EXAMPLE ONLY</h4>

<p>Ordinary tourists, alien, looking out the window outside into space, leaning against the wall: <em>Where‚Äôs the vomit bag on this junker?!</em></p>

<h4 id="set-no6-example-only">Set No.6 EXAMPLE ONLY</h4>

<p>Talk about rumors of THE BOX being found and whether its a good or bad thing. Will it save everyone, or is it just a rumor: <em>‚ÄúThe box‚Ä¶sounds like something I tossed my trash in last week. No‚Ä¶maybe its something more sexy‚Äù</em></p>

